# AlltagsEngel — Cursor Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router) — `app/` directory, NO `src/` folder
- React 19, TypeScript
- Supabase (Auth + Database + RLS)
- @supabase/ssr for server-side auth

## Project Structure
- NO `App.tsx` — This is Next.js App Router, not CRA/Vite
- `app/layout.tsx` = Root layout (fonts, metadata, global CSS) — equivalent of App.tsx
- `app/page.tsx` = Homepage
- Each folder under `app/` is a route (file-based routing)
- Route groups: `app/(kunde)/`, `app/(engel)/`, `app/admin/`, `app/mis/`
- Each route group can have its own `layout.tsx`

## Key Files
- `app/layout.tsx` — Root layout, Jost + Cormorant fonts, LayoutWrapper
- `middleware.ts` — Auth protection for /kunde, /engel, /admin, /mis routes
- `lib/supabase/client.ts` — Browser Supabase client
- `lib/supabase/server.ts` — Server Supabase client (cookies)
- `components/LayoutWrapper.tsx` — Conditional navbar/footer wrapper

## Auth & Roles
- Supabase Auth (email/password)
- Roles: admin, engel, kunde (stored in profiles table)
- Middleware checks role for /admin and /mis routes
- RLS policies on profiles table use JWT user_metadata for role checks

## Language
- UI text: German (Deutsch)
- Code comments / dev communication: Turkish or German
- Commit messages: Turkish or German

## Rules
- Always commit and push after changes
- Use `'use client'` directive for client components
- Server components are default in App Router
- Supabase client: use `createClient()` from `@/lib/supabase/client` in client components
- Supabase server: use `createClient()` from `@/lib/supabase/server` in server components
